  <text>
    <p>
Let [mathjaxinline]f(x) = 1[/mathjaxinline]. Using the inner product on the vector space [mathjaxinline]C[0,2][/mathjaxinline] as defined earlier, calculate [mathjaxinline]\| f\|[/mathjaxinline]. </p>
    <p>
      <numericalresponse answer="sqrt(2)">
        <textline>
          <responseparam type="tolerance" default=".01"/>
        </textline>
      </numericalresponse>
    </p>
    <p>
      <solution>
        <font color="blue">Answer: </font>
        <font color="blue">
          <table id="a0000000148" class="equation" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="7" style="table-layout:auto">
            <tr>
              <td class="equation" style="width:80%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;border-style:hidden">[mathjax]\| f\|  = \sqrt {\langle f, f\rangle } = \sqrt {\int _0^2 f(x)^2 \  dx} = \sqrt {\int _0^2 1 \  dx} = \sqrt {2}.[/mathjax]</td>
              <td class="eqnnum" style="width:20%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:left;border-style:hidden"/>
            </tr>
          </table>
        </font>
      </solution>
    </p>
  </text>
</problem>
